text.section:
The purpose of the Lida Lee Tall Learning Resources Center is to provide an accessible laboratory environment for:
Training students from public institutions of higher education to be teachers in elementary schools by providing students the opportunity for early field experience;
Identifying and addressing appropriate early childhood and elementary education research needs and priorities in this State;
Providing opportunities for demonstration and observation of effective teaching practices; and
Providing in-service and staff development opportunities for faculty from teacher education programs, prospective principals and experienced teachers in Maryland elementary schools.

The Governor shall appoint a board of trustees to govern the Lida Lee Tall Learning Resources Center who shall:
Establish policy and exercise general control over the Lida Lee Tall Learning Resources Center;
Appoint the principal and, upon the recommendation of the principal, appoint all professional and support staff and determine the salaries of the professional and support staff;
Authorize the curricula to be used;
Determine admission requirements for students;
Set tuition; and
Encourage collaboration between the Lida Lee Tall Learning Resources Center and the public institutions of higher education in Maryland.

section.section:
The Board of Trustees shall consist of 11 members. Of the members:
3 shall be board members, officers, or employees of institutions of higher education in the State of Maryland;
3 shall be board members, officers, or employees of local education agencies in the State of Maryland;
1 shall be a Board member, officer, or employee of the Maryland State Department of Education;
1 shall be a Board member, officer, or employee of the Maryland Higher Education Commission;
1 shall be the current President of the Lida Lee Tall Learning Resources Center Parent-Teacher Association; and
2 shall be public members.
